# Chapter 22 — Job & Industry Requirements
### (Cybersecurity / Ethical Hacking Perspective)

This chapter maps everything learned so far (Chapters 1–21) to real career paths, certifications, and what employers actually look for in networking-security roles.

---

## 1. Common Cybersecurity Job Roles (Networking-Heavy)

| Role | Focus | Networking Skills Required |
|---|---|---|
| **SOC Analyst (Tier 1/2)** | Monitor alerts, triage incidents | Protocol knowledge, packet analysis, log/SIEM basics |
| **Penetration Tester** | Simulate attacks to find vulnerabilities | Deep protocol/OSI knowledge, scanning tools, exploitation |
| **Network Security Engineer** | Design/maintain secure network infrastructure | Firewalls, VLANs, routing, VPNs, device hardening |
| **Red Teamer** | Simulate advanced, persistent real-world attackers | All of the above + social engineering, evasion techniques |
| **Blue Teamer / Defender** | Detect and respond to attacks | IDS/IPS, traffic analysis, incident response |
| **Vulnerability Analyst** | Identify and prioritize vulnerabilities | Scanning tools, CVSS scoring, patch management understanding |
| **Cloud Security Engineer** | Secure cloud-hosted networks/infrastructure | Networking fundamentals applied to VPCs, cloud firewalls, IAM |
| **IoT/OT Security Specialist** | Secure industrial/embedded device networks | Chapter 18 concepts, specialized protocols (Modbus, MQTT) |

